 instances, the uncertainties of the essential transit\nparameters are also reduced. For HAT-P-23b, in particular, we derive a planet\nsize 4.5 +- 1.0% smaller. We also derive improved linear periods for each\nsystem, useful for scheduling observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Jan 2016 01:09:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-09"}
